===Lyapunov CLT===
In this variant of the central limit theorem the random variables formula_40 have to be independent, but not necessarily identically distributed. The theorem also requires that random variables formula_41 have moments of some order and that the rate of growth of these moments is limited by the Lyapunov condition given below.

 \, \sum_{i=1}^{n} \operatorname E\left[\left|X_{i} - \mu_{i}\right|^{2+\delta}\right] = 0&lt;/math&gt;
is satisfied, then a sum of formula_42 converges in distribution to a standard normal random variable, as formula_43 goes to infinity:
formula_44}}

